^["stream"]{
 >>[2026-04-11 04:25] observe — Current defaults are still richer than the calm preset, mobile header disclosure relies on wrapping, and diagnostics/state blocks stay visually present longer than needed.
 >>[2026-04-11 04:26] decide — Keep new shell and brace behavior in dedicated modules so site.js stays wiring-only.
 >>[2026-04-11 04:44] implement — Added shared shell disclosure and brace-edge action modules, wired them through site.js, and shifted runtime defaults toward the calm baseline.
 >>[2026-04-11 04:45] implement — Refactored the state inspector into a collapsible/dismissable diagnostic surface with restore controls and collapsed-by-default behavior when cognitive handles are off.
 >>[2026-04-11 04:47] taste — Container surfaces now read flatter and more statement-like through top-line syntax rules instead of heavier floating-card treatment.
 >>[2026-04-11 04:49] verify — node --check passed for site.js, site-settings.js, spw-shell-disclosure.js, spw-brace-actions.js, and spw-state-inspector.js; git diff --check passed.
 >>[2026-04-11 13:12] integrate — Minimal defaults now hide the console, the settings page checked states match runtime defaults before JS boots, and statement-line treatment extends to presets, categories, operator cards, mode panels, and smart resonance cards.
}

